FBIS4-63989 "drsov103_a_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS U.S., Germany Offer Help Building Nuclear Waste Site U.S., Germany Offer Help Building Nuclear Waste Site LD2605145594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 26 May 94 LD2605145594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] The Americans have offered Russia assistance in building a burial site for radioactive waste. However, they have also stated that nuclear waste from the United States should be accepted at the burial site as a condition for doing so. Germany has also come forward with a similar proposal. Viktor Kutsenko, a representative of the Ministry of Environmental Protection and Natural Resources, said this in an interview for the RIA agency. He stressed that Russia would not agree to the country being turned into a dumping ground for nuclear waste.
